{# Base HTML layout — table-based for cross-client compatibility.

   Every per-email template extends this and overrides the
   ``content`` block. The visible structure is:

     [ olive-tinted header bar with the "Trust Halal" wordmark ]
     [ white body card with the message content                ]
     [ muted footer with site link + copyright                 ]

   Inline styles only on the elements that need them — most
   modern email clients support <style> blocks now (2024+) but a
   handful still strip them. Inline keeps the visual fidelity
   guaranteed; the <style> block at the top is a progressive
   enhancement for clients that respect it (better dark-mode
   handling, hover states on the button).

   Required context variables for every template that extends
   this one:

     * ``preheader`` — short summary text shown by inbox clients
       between the subject and the body preview. Caller MUST set
       this; an unset preheader leaks the first line of the body
       which is usually awkward.
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>{{ subject_for_preview | default(preheader) }}</title>
  <style>
    /* Tiny hover-state polish for the CTA button. Clients that
       strip <style> just don't get the hover; the inline color
       stays. */
    .th-button:hover {
      background-color: #5a7332 !important;
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      .th-card { background-color: #1a1a1a !important; }
      .th-card-text { color: #e6e6e6 !important; }
      .th-muted { color: #999 !important; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body style="margin: 0; padding: 0; background-color: #faf9f6; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif; color: #1a1a1a; -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">
  {# Preheader — hidden text shown in inbox previews, prevents the
     client from leaking footer copy or the first body line into the
     summary slot. ``display:none`` keeps it out of the visible body. #}
  <div style="display: none; max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; mso-hide: all;">
    {{ preheader }}
  </div>

  <table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" style="background-color: #faf9f6;">
    <tr>
      <td align="center" style="padding: 24px 16px;">
        {# Outer container — 600 px is the safe max width for email. #}
        <table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="600" style="max-width: 600px; width: 100%;">
          {# Header — wordmark on an olive band. #}
          <tr>
            <td align="left" style="padding: 8px 4px 16px 4px;">
              <a href="https://trusthalal.org" style="text-decoration: none; color: #6f8b3e; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                Trust Halal
              </a>
            </td>
          </tr>

          {# Body card — white background, rounded corners, subtle
             border. Caller writes Markdown-y prose inside the
             ``content`` block; we don't try to template every UI
             primitive (button, divider) — instead the per-email
             template hand-writes them with inline styles matching
             this card's typography. #}
          <tr>
            <td class="th-card" style="background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #ececec; border-radius: 12px; padding: 32px 28px;">
              <div class="th-card-text" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55; color: #1a1a1a;">
                {% block content %}{% endblock %}
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>

          {# Footer. ``site_url`` is auto-resolved from a Jinja global
             registered in ``email.py`` (defaults to halalfoodnearme.com)
             so each per-email template doesn't have to pass it
             individually. #}
          <tr>
            <td align="center" style="padding: 24px 16px 8px 16px;">
              <p class="th-muted" style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5; color: #888;">
                Trust Halal — verified halal data for restaurants you can trust.
              </p>
              {# A named human route, not just Reply. Reply-To covers the
                 common case, but it's invisible — someone forwarding this,
                 or reading it somewhere that hides headers, had no way to
                 reach us at all. The people most likely to want one are the
                 ones whose claim was rejected or whose review came down. #}
              <p class="th-muted" style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5; color: #888;">
                Questions? <a href="mailto:support@trusthalal.org" style="color: #888; text-decoration: underline;">support@trusthalal.org</a>
              </p>
              <p class="th-muted" style="margin: 0; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5; color: #888;">
                <a href="https://halalfoodnearme.com" style="color: #888; text-decoration: underline;">halalfoodnearme.com</a>
                &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <a href="https://trusthalal.org" style="color: #888; text-decoration: underline;">trusthalal.org</a>
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
